  "correctAnswer": "C",
  "section": "Math",
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Set up",
      "content": "Start with $r = \\sqrt{8w - 3}$. Square both sides to remove the radical: $r^2 = 8w - 3$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Solve",
      "content": "Add 3: $r^2 + 3 = 8w$. Divide by 8: $$w = \\frac{r^2 + 3}{8}$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Answer",
      "content": "<strong>C</strong> is correct."
    }
  ]
}